    {
      "number": 1,
      "title": "ZAB Appeal: 2274 Shattuck Avenue, Use Permit #ZP2023-0079",
      "action": "M/S/C (Blackaby/Humbert) to close the public hearing. Vote: Ayes \u2013 Kesarwani, Bartlett, Tregub, O\u2019Keefe, Blackaby, Lunaparra, Humbert, Ishii; Noes \u2013 None; Abstain \u2013 None; Recused \u2013 Taplin (Recused for Potential Conflict of Interest). Action: M/S/C (O\u2019Keefe/Humbert) to adopt Resolution No. 71,725-N.S. affirming the Zoning Adjustments Board decision to approve Use Permit #ZP2023-0079 to demolish the commercial building (preserving and renovating the front fa\u00e7ade and lobby), and construct a 17-story (183 feet, plus 5-foot parapet), 214,032-square-foot, mixed-use residential building with 227 dwelling units (including 23 Very Low-Income Density Bonus qualifying units), and one ADA parking space, and dismiss the appeal. Vote: Ayes \u2013 Kesarwani, Bartlett, Tregub, O\u2019Keefe, Blackaby, Lunaparra, Humbert, Ishii; Noes \u2013 None; Abstain \u2013 None; Recused \u2013 Taplin (Recused for Potential C onflict of Interest). Tuesday, April 22, 2025 ANNOTATED AGENDA Page 2 Adjournment Action: M/S/C (Blackaby/Humbert) to adjourn the meeting. Vote: Ayes \u2013 Kesarwani, Bartlett, Tregub, O\u2019Keefe, Blackaby, Lunaparra, Humbert, Ishii; Noes \u2013 None; Abstain \u2013 None; Recused \u2013 Taplin (Recused for Potential Conflict of Interest). Adjourned at 8:51 p.m. Communications Item #1: ZAB Appeal: 2274 Shattuck Avenue, Use Permit #ZP2023-0079",
